Use the standard library
This is how to filter_by_substring of strings and substring:
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that i is 0

   Do this strings's length times:
      Remember that s is item i in strings
      Remember that found is no
      Remember that j is 0

      Do this s's length times:
         When found is yes, then:
            Leave the loop
         End when

         When sum of j and substring's length is at most s's length, then:
            Remember that matches is yes
            Remember that k is 0

            Do this substring's length times:
               When item (sum of j and k) in s is not item k in substring, then:
                  Remember that matches is no
                  Leave the loop
               End when
               Increase k
            End do

            When matches is yes, then:
               Remember that found is yes
            End when
         End when

         Increase j
      End do

      When found is yes, then:
         Add result to s
      End when

      Increase i
   End do

   The answer is result
